  const { products, syncedAt } = await getCachedProducts();

  // ...render
}
```

This gives:
- Immediate response to the admin (form submits, page stays interactive)
- First revalidation so the page can show slightly refreshed data
- Background sync continues
- Second revalidation when sync completes
- Eventual consistency across views (all use same "products" tag)

This is the best pattern that matches the requirements. Let me implement it.

